lease-readiness\"]\n    },\n    \"ai-council-aliases\": {\n      \"keywords\": [\"deep-ai-council\", \"ai council deliberation\", \"multi-seat planning council\", \"council convergence\", \"planning council\"]\n    },\n    \"agent-improvement-aliases\": {\n      \"keywords\": [\"improve agent\", \"evaluate agent\", \"agent scoring\", \"score agent candidate\", \"promote or rollback agent change\", \"agent-improvement\"]\n    },\n    \"model-benchmark-aliases\": {\n      \"keywords\": [\"model benchmark\", \"benchmark a model\", \"prompt framework benchmark\", \"benchmark-harness\"]\n    },\n    \"skill-benchmark-aliases\": {\n      \"keywords\": [\"skill benchmark\", \"benchmark a skill\", \"skill routing benchmark\"]\n    },\n    \"ai-system-improvement-aliases\": {\n      \"keywords\": [\"non-dev ai system\", \"non-dev-ai-system\", \"package ai system benchmark\"]\n    }\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":78,"totalLines":78,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/hub-router.json","time":{"start":1783437244180,"end":1783437244188}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0076295aaea6008d016a4d17bc0654819184eda50347a4c54b"}},"id":"prt_f3d24b6fe001hS8186M3TdwaNB","sessionID":"ses_0c2dd1dfcffeawJ3GCJmwMFkLa","messageID":"msg_f3d248d2f001CSnH4zt1csBz6w"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783437244206,"sessionID":"ses_0c2dd1dfcffeawJ3GCJmwMFkLa","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BzT5zA2OXyxGviIwEvEi98Br","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/mode-registry.json","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/mode-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"skill\": \"sk-code\",\n3:   \"version\": \"4.1.0.0\",\n4:   \"description\": \"Declarative two-axis mode registry for the sk-code parent hub. Every packet is a modes[] entry carrying the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) plus its advisorRouting contract. The WORKFLOW axis (quality/code-review) is process; the SURFACE axis (code-webflow/code-opencode) is read-only domain evidence. Implement/debug/verify phase doctrine is consolidated in shared/references/workflow_*.md, symlinked into each surface. The advisor routes the single identity sk-code; the hub resolves the workflow mode and bundles surface packets as evidence.\",\n5:   \"discriminator\": {\n6:     \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n7:     \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for process modes that act, 'surface' for read-only domain-evidence packets bundled alongside a workflow mode.\",\n8:     \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: surface-router for surface-aware code workflows, review-cache for review output caching, evidence-base for read-only surface packets.\"\n9:   },\n10:   \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n11:     \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-code every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-code and the hub picks the mode. Surface packets are advisor-invisible and reached only by hub bundling.\",\n12:     \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. Folder equals packetSkillName for every mode.\",\n13:     \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"false for every mode because folder equals packetSkillName.\"\n14:   },\n15:   \"extensions\": {\n16:     \"surface-axis\": {\n17:       \"description\": \"Declares the SURFACE axis. packetKind:'surface' entries are read-only domain-evidence packets (backendKind:'evidence-base', routingClass:'metadata', mutatesWorkspace:false) bundled alongside a workflow mode via routerPolicy.outcomes.surfaceBundle. They carry stack knowledge, never process.\",\n18:       \"surfaces\": [\"code-webflow\", \"code-opencode\"]\n19:     }\n20:   },\n21:   \"modes\": [\n22:     {\n23:       \"workflowMode\": \"quality\",\n24:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n25:       \"backendKind\": \"surface-router\",\n26:       \"toolSurface\": {\n27:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\"],\n28:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Task\"],\n29:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n30:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n31:       },\n32:       \"packet\": \"code-quality\",\n33:       \"packetSkillName\": \"code-quality\",\n34:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n35:       \"aliases\": [\"quality gate\", \"code quality\", \"comment hygiene check\", \"surface checklist\", \"p0 p1 p2 author check\", \"stack-specific code quality gate\", \"alignment verifier\", \"stable jsonl keys\", \"quality check\", \"check before done\", \"author quality gate\", \"pre-verification quality check\", \"p0 p1 p2 review\"],\n36:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n37:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n38:         \"packetSkillName\": \"code-quality\"\n39:       }\n40:     },\n41:     {\n42:       \"workflowMode\": \"code-review\",\n43:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n44:       \"backendKind\": \"review-cache\",\n45:       \"toolSurface\": {\n46:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Write\"],\n47:         \"forbidden\": [\"Edit\", \"Task\"],\n48:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n49:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n50:       },\n51:       \"packet\": \"code-review\",\n52:       \"packetSkillName\": \"code-review\",\n53:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n54:       \"aliases\": [\"code review\", \"reviewer\", \"findings-first review\", \"security review\", \"pr review\", \"review baseline\", \"correctness review\", \"test quality review\", \"review output contract\", \"pr-state gates\"],\n55:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n56:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n57:         \"packetSkillName\": \"code-review\"\n58:       }\n59:     },\n60:     {\n61:       \"workflowMode\": \"code-webflow\",\n62:       \"packetKind\": \"surface\",\n63:       \"backendKind\": \"evidence-base\",\n64:       \"toolSurface\": {\n65:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\"],\n66:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Task\"],\n67:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n68:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n69:       },\n70:       \"packet\": \"code-webflow\",\n71:       \"packetSkillName\": \"code-webflow\",\n72:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n73:       \"aliases\": [\"webflow implementation\", \"frontend implementation standards\", \"webflow frontend workflow\"],\n74:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n75:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n76:         \"packetSkillName\": \"code-webflow\"\n77:       }\n78:     },\n79:     {\n80:       \"workflowMode\": \"code-opencode\",\n81:       \"packetKind\": \"surface\",\n82:       \"backendKind\": \"evidence-base\",\n83:       \"toolSurface\": {\n84:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\"],\n85:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Task\"],\n86:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n87:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n88:       },\n89:       \"packet\": \"code-opencode\",\n90:       \"packetSkillName\": \"code-opencode\",\n91:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n92:       \"aliases\": [\"opencode system code\", \"opencode system code workflow\", \"opencode typescript verification\"],\n93:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n94:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n95:         \"packetSkillName\": \"code-opencode\"\n96:       }\n97:     }\n98:   ]\n99: }\n\n(End of file - total 99 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"skill\": \"sk-code\",\n  \"version\": \"4.1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Declarative two-axis mode registry for the sk-code parent hub. Every packet is a modes[] entry carrying the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) plus its advisorRouting contract. The WORKFLOW axis (quality/code-review) is process; the SURFACE axis (code-webflow/code-opencode) is read-only domain evidence. Implement/debug/verify phase doctrine is consolidated in shared/references/workflow_*.md, symlinked into each surface. The advisor routes the single identity sk-code; the hub resolves the workflow mode and bundles surface packets as evidence.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for process modes that act, 'surface' for read-only domain-evidence packets bundled alongside a workflow mode.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: surface-router for surface-aware code workflows, review-cache for review output caching, evidence-base for read-only surface packets.\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-code every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-code and the hub picks the mode. Surface packets are advisor-invisible and reached only by hub bundling.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. Folder equals packetSkillName for every mode.\",\n    \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"false for every mode because folder equals packetSkillName.\"\n  },\n  \"extensions\": {\n    \"surface-axis\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the SURFACE axis. packetKind:'surface' entries are read-only domain-evidence packets (backendKind:'evidence-base', routingClass:'metadata', mutatesWorkspace:false) bundled alongside a workflow mode via routerPolicy.outcomes.surfaceBundle. They carry stack knowledge, never process.\",\n      \"surfaces\": [\"code-webflow\", \"code-opencode\"]\n    }\n  },","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/mode-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"skill\": \"sk-code\",\n  \"version\": \"4.1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Declarative two-axis mode registry for the sk-code parent hub. Every packet is a modes[] entry carrying the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) plus its advisorRouting contract. The WORKFLOW axis (quality/code-review) is process; the SURFACE axis (code-webflow/code-opencode) is read-only domain evidence. Implement/debug/verify phase doctrine is consolidated in shared/references/workflow_*.md, symlinked into each surface. The advisor routes the single identity sk-code; the hub resolves the workflow mode and bundles surface packets as evidence.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for process modes that act, 'surface' for read-only domain-evidence packets bundled alongside a workflow mode.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: surface-router for surface-aware code workflows, review-cache for review output caching, evidence-base for read-only surface packets.\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-code every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-code and the hub picks the mode. Surface packets are advisor-invisible and reached only by hub bundling.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. Folder equals packetSkillName for every mode.\",\n    \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"false for every mode because folder equals packetSkillName.\"\n  },\n  \"extensions\": {\n    \"surface-axis\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the SURFACE axis. packetKind:'surface' entries are read-only domain-evidence packets (backendKind:'evidence-base', routingClass:'metadata', mutatesWorkspace:false) bundled alongside a workflow mode via routerPolicy.outcomes.surfaceBundle. They carry stack knowledge, never process.\",\n      \"surfaces\": [\"code-webflow\", \"code-opencode\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"modes\": [\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"quality\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"surface-router\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Task\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"code-quality\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"code-quality\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"aliases\": [\"quality gate\", \"code quality\", \"comment hygiene check\", \"surface checklist\", \"p0 p1 p2 author check\", \"stack-specific code quality gate\", \"alignment verifier\", \"stable jsonl keys\", \"quality check\", \"check before done\", \"author quality gate\", \"pre-verification quality check\", \"p0 p1 p2 review\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"code-quality\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"code-review\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"review-cache\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Write\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Edit\", \"Task\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"code-review\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"code-review\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"aliases\": [\"code review\", \"reviewer\", \"findings-first review\", \"security review\", \"pr review\", \"review baseline\", \"correctness review\", \"test quality review\", \"review output contract\", \"pr-state gates\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"code-review\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"code-webflow\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"surface\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"evidence-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Task\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"code-webflow\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"code-webflow\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"aliases\": [\"webflow implementation\", \"frontend implementation standards\", \"webflow frontend workflow\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"code-webflow\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"code-opencode\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"surface\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"evidence-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Task\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"code-opencode\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"code-opencode\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"aliases\": [\"opencode system code\", \"opencode system code workflow\", \"opencode typescript verification\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"code-opencode\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":99,"totalLines":99,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/mode-registry.json","time":{"start":1783437244192,"end":1783437244201}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0076295aaea6008d016a4d17bc06608191ac51fcfc93f9e971"}},"id":"prt_f3d24b7160015L5eofjr4MnOqA","sessionID":"ses_0c2dd1dfcffeawJ3GCJmwMFkLa","messageID":"msg_f3d248d2f001CSnH4zt1csBz6w"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783437244206,"sessionID":"ses_0c2dd1dfcffeawJ3GCJmwMFkLa","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1R1EHy1aPRwnWGZjqnXiUVyQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json","offset":1,"limit":320},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"skill\": \"sk-design\",\n3:   \"version\": \"1.4.0.0\",\n4:   \"description\": \"Declarative mode registry: the single source of truth for the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) PLUS the advisorRouting projection for sk-design. The hub reads this file to resolve a mode; the advisor routes any design query to the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode. All six modes route by hub membership (routingClass 'metadata'), so there is no advisor map entry per mode and no merged-identity projection — the advisor does not read this file at runtime.\",\n5:   \"discriminator\": {\n6:     \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n7:     \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for the five design-judgment modes (interface/foundations/motion/audit/md-generator) that act on a design axis; 'transport' for a packet that bridges to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface rather than performing design judgment itself.\",\n8:     \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: reference-base (cites the shared design reference base under references/), playwright-extract (runs the embedded Playwright CSS-extraction pipeline), or od-cli-transport (drives the external Open Design app's od CLI and stdio MCP server).\"\n9:   },\n10:   \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n11:     \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-design every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode, so no mode carries an advisor map entry or a merged-identity projection.\",\n12:     \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. The original flat skill name is preserved as packetSkillName; the packet folder is the short mode key, so folder != packetSkillName is grandfathered here and recorded per mode via grandfatheredFolderMismatch.\",\n13:     \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"true when the packet folder (short mode key, e.g. 'interface') differs from packetSkillName (the preserved flat name, e.g. 'interface'). All five sk-design modes preserve their original flat names (folder == packetSkillName), so none has a folder mismatch — grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false for all five (there is no mismatch to grandfather).\",\n14:     \"command\": \"The bound slash command for the mode, recorded even on metadata-routed modes (same field sk-doc's mode-registry.json carries); null when the mode has no dedicated command today. All five sk-design modes have a dedicated command as of the Phase 015 router+assets build, so this field is never null here.\"\n15:   },\n16:   \"extensions\": {\n17:     \"transform-verbs\": {\n18:       \"description\": \"Declares the transform-verb routing extension: framing-split verb aliases (interface-frame 'make it' applies the move; audit-frame 'should it be' evaluates it), with excludedAliases and aliasOnly carve-outs. Activates the in-place top-level transformVerbRouting block without relocating it — the hub router vocabulary, command projection parity, and playbook scenarios all read it at that location.\",\n19:       \"declaredField\": \"transformVerbRouting\"\n20:     },\n21:     \"transport-axis\": {\n22:       \"description\": \"Declares the TRANSPORT axis. packetKind:'transport' entries bridge to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface (backendKind:'od-cli-transport', routingClass:'metadata', mutatesWorkspace:false since writes land in the external tool, not this repo). They never perform design judgment themselves — every entry on this axis has its own mandatory-pairing contract requiring sk-design's own workflow modes before any design-affecting operation.\",\n23:       \"transports\": [\"design-mcp-open-design\"]\n24:     }\n25:   },\n26:   \"transformVerbRouting\": {\n27:     \"note\": \"Transform verbs split by framing: audit asks whether the move should happen; interface applies the requested move.\",\n28:     \"interfaceFrame\": \"make it\",\n29:     \"auditFrame\": \"should it be\",\n30:     \"interfaceAliases\": [\"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"clarify\", \"delight\"],\n31:     \"aliasOnly\": [\"clarify\"],\n32:     \"commandProjectionParity\": [\"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"delight\"],\n33:     \"excludedAliases\": {\n34:       \"foundations\": [\"typeset\", \"colorize\"],\n35:       \"audit\": [\"harden\", \"polish\"]\n36:     }\n37:   },\n38:   \"modes\": [\n39:     {\n40:       \"workflowMode\": \"interface\",\n41:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n42:       \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n43:       \"toolSurface\": {\n44:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n45:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n46:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n47:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n48:       },\n49:       \"packet\": \"design-interface\",\n50:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-interface/procedures\",\n51:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\",\n52:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n53:       \"command\": \"/design:interface\",\n54:       \"aliases\": [\"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"visual identity\", \"make it look good\", \"looks templated\", \"redesign the ui\", \"hero section\", \"landing page direction\", \"hero redesign\", \"ui build\", \"design variations\", \"less generic\", \"custom not templated\", \"visual direction\", \"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"clarify\", \"delight\"],\n55:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n56:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n57:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\"\n58:       }\n59:     },\n60:     {\n61:       \"workflowMode\": \"foundations\",\n62:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n63:       \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n64:       \"toolSurface\": {\n65:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n66:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n67:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n68:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n69:       },\n70:       \"packet\": \"design-foundations\",\n71:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-foundations/procedures\",\n72:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-foundations\",\n73:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n74:       \"command\": \"/design:foundations\",\n75:       \"aliases\": [\"design foundations\", \"color system\", \"oklch palette\", \"color token system\", \"dark mode palette\", \"typography scale\", \"font pairing\", \"spacing system\", \"layout rhythm\", \"information hierarchy\", \"responsive layout\", \"design tokens\", \"theme tokens\", \"grid\", \"container queries\", \"context adaptation\", \"data visualization\", \"chart type\", \"data tables\", \"token starter\"],\n76:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n77:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n78:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-foundations\"\n79:       }\n80:     },\n81:     {\n82:       \"workflowMode\": \"motion\",\n83:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n84:       \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n85:       \"toolSurface\": {\n86:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n87:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n88:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n89:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n90:       },\n91:       \"packet\": \"design-motion\",\n92:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-motion/procedures\",\n93:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-motion\",\n94:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n95:       \"command\": \"/design:motion\",\n96:       \"aliases\": [\"motion design\", \"animate this\", \"micro-interactions\", \"transitions\", \"interaction states\", \"hover state\", \"focus state\", \"loading state\", \"choreography\", \"motion budget\", \"AnimatePresence\", \"exit animation\", \"reduced motion\", \"morphing icons\", \"motion performance\"],\n97:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n98:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n99:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-motion\"\n100:       }\n101:     },\n102:     {\n103:       \"workflowMode\": \"audit\",\n104:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n105:       \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n106:       \"toolSurface\": {\n107:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n108:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n109:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n110:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n111:       },\n112:       \"packet\": \"design-audit\",\n113:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-audit/procedures\",\n114:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-audit\",\n115:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n116:       \"command\": \"/design:audit\",\n117:       \"aliases\": [\"design audit\", \"ui critique\", \"design review\", \"review the ui\", \"audit the design\", \"accessibility audit\", \"wcag contrast\", \"performance audit\", \"anti-slop detection\", \"ai tell\", \"production hardening\", \"design quality score\", \"ui quality review\", \"P0 P1 design findings\"],\n118:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n119:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n120:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-audit\"\n121:       }\n122:     },\n123:     {\n124:       \"workflowMode\": \"md-generator\",\n125:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n126:       \"backendKind\": \"playwright-extract\",\n127:       \"toolSurface\": {\n128:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n129:         \"forbidden\": [],\n130:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n131:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n132:       },\n133:       \"packet\": \"design-md-generator\",\n134:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-md-generator/procedures\",\n135:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-md-generator\",\n136:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n137:       \"command\": \"/design:md-generator\",\n138:       \"aliases\": [\"extract design system\", \"generate design.md\", \"capture website css\", \"design tokens from url\", \"create design reference\", \"style reference\", \"tokens.json\", \"design-to-markdown\", \"extract design tokens\", \"validate design.md\", \"design.md validation\", \"design fidelity check\", \"design.md report\", \"render design preview\", \"source of truth\", \"study design.md format\"],\n139:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n140:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n141:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-md-generator\"\n142:       }\n143:     },\n144:     {\n145:       \"workflowMode\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n146:       \"packetKind\": \"transport\",\n147:       \"backendKind\": \"od-cli-transport\",\n148:       \"toolSurface\": {\n149:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\"],\n150:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\"],\n151:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n152:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n153:       },\n154:       \"packet\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n155:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n156:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n157:       \"command\": null,\n158:       \"aliases\": [\"open design\", \"open-design\", \"od mcp\", \"od cli\", \"wire open design\", \"connect open design\", \"drive open design from the terminal\", \"design system from open design\"],\n159:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n160:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n161:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-mcp-open-design\"\n162:       }\n163:     }\n164:   ]\n165: }\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"skill\": \"sk-design\",\n  \"version\": \"1.4.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Declarative mode registry: the single source of truth for the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) PLUS the advisorRouting projection for sk-design. The hub reads this file to resolve a mode; the advisor routes any design query to the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode. All six modes route by hub membership (routingClass 'metadata'), so there is no advisor map entry per mode and no merged-identity projection — the advisor does not read this file at runtime.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for the five design-judgment modes (interface/foundations/motion/audit/md-generator) that act on a design axis; 'transport' for a packet that bridges to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface rather than performing design judgment itself.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: reference-base (cites the shared design reference base under references/), playwright-extract (runs the embedded Playwright CSS-extraction pipeline), or od-cli-transport (drives the external Open Design app's od CLI and stdio MCP server).\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-design every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode, so no mode carries an advisor map entry or a merged-identity projection.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. The original flat skill name is preserved as packetSkillName; the packet folder is the short mode key, so folder != packetSkillName is grandfathered here and recorded per mode via grandfatheredFolderMismatch.\",\n    \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"true when the packet folder (short mode key, e.g. 'interface') differs from packetSkillName (the preserved flat name, e.g. 'interface'). All five sk-design modes preserve their original flat names (folder == packetSkillName), so none has a folder mismatch — grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false for all five (there is no mismatch to grandfather).\",\n    \"command\": \"The bound slash command for the mode, recorded even on metadata-routed modes (same field sk-doc's mode-registry.json carries); null when the mode has no dedicated command today. All five sk-design modes have a dedicated command as of the Phase 015 router+assets build, so this field is never null here.\"\n  },\n  \"extensions\": {\n    \"transform-verbs\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the transform-verb routing extension: framing-split verb aliases (interface-frame 'make it' applies the move; audit-frame 'should it be' evaluates it), with excludedAliases and aliasOnly carve-outs. Activates the in-place top-level transformVerbRouting block without relocating it — the hub router vocabulary, command projection parity, and playbook scenarios all read it at that location.\",\n      \"declaredField\": \"transformVerbRouting\"\n    },","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"skill\": \"sk-design\",\n  \"version\": \"1.4.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Declarative mode registry: the single source of truth for the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) PLUS the advisorRouting projection for sk-design. The hub reads this file to resolve a mode; the advisor routes any design query to the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode. All six modes route by hub membership (routingClass 'metadata'), so there is no advisor map entry per mode and no merged-identity projection — the advisor does not read this file at runtime.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for the five design-judgment modes (interface/foundations/motion/audit/md-generator) that act on a design axis; 'transport' for a packet that bridges to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface rather than performing design judgment itself.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: reference-base (cites the shared design reference base under references/), playwright-extract (runs the embedded Playwright CSS-extraction pipeline), or od-cli-transport (drives the external Open Design app's od CLI and stdio MCP server).\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-design every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode, so no mode carries an advisor map entry or a merged-identity projection.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. The original flat skill name is preserved as packetSkillName; the packet folder is the short mode key, so folder != packetSkillName is grandfathered here and recorded per mode via grandfatheredFolderMismatch.\",\n    \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"true when the packet folder (short mode key, e.g. 'interface') differs from packetSkillName (the preserved flat name, e.g. 'interface'). All five sk-design modes preserve their original flat names (folder == packetSkillName), so none has a folder mismatch — grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false for all five (there is no mismatch to grandfather).\",\n    \"command\": \"The bound slash command for the mode, recorded even on metadata-routed modes (same field sk-doc's mode-registry.json carries); null when the mode has no dedicated command today. All five sk-design modes have a dedicated command as of the Phase 015 router+assets build, so this field is never null here.\"\n  },\n  \"extensions\": {\n    \"transform-verbs\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the transform-verb routing extension: framing-split verb aliases (interface-frame 'make it' applies the move; audit-frame 'should it be' evaluates it), with excludedAliases and aliasOnly carve-outs. Activates the in-place top-level transformVerbRouting block without relocating it — the hub router vocabulary, command projection parity, and playbook scenarios all read it at that location.\",\n      \"declaredField\": \"transformVerbRouting\"\n    },\n    \"transport-axis\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the TRANSPORT axis. packetKind:'transport' entries bridge to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface (backendKind:'od-cli-transport', routingClass:'metadata', mutatesWorkspace:false since writes land in the external tool, not this repo). They never perform design judgment themselves — every entry on this axis has its own mandatory-pairing contract requiring sk-design's own workflow modes before any design-affecting operation.\",\n      \"transports\": [\"design-mcp-open-design\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"transformVerbRouting\": {\n    \"note\": \"Transform verbs split by framing: audit asks whether the move should happen; interface applies the requested move.\",\n    \"interfaceFrame\": \"make it\",\n    \"auditFrame\": \"should it be\",\n    \"interfaceAliases\": [\"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"clarify\", \"delight\"],\n    \"aliasOnly\": [\"clarify\"],\n    \"commandProjectionParity\": [\"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"delight\"],\n    \"excludedAliases\": {\n      \"foundations\": [\"typeset\", \"colorize\"],\n      \"audit\": [\"harden\", \"polish\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"modes\": [\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"interface\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-interface\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-interface/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:interface\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"visual identity\", \"make it look good\", \"looks templated\", \"redesign the ui\", \"hero section\", \"landing page direction\", \"hero redesign\", \"ui build\", \"design variations\", \"less generic\", \"custom not templated\", \"visual direction\", \"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"clarify\", \"delight\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"foundations\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-foundations\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-foundations/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-foundations\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:foundations\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"design foundations\", \"color system\", \"oklch palette\", \"color token system\", \"dark mode palette\", \"typography scale\", \"font pairing\", \"spacing system\", \"layout rhythm\", \"information hierarchy\", \"responsive layout\", \"design tokens\", \"theme tokens\", \"grid\", \"container queries\", \"context adaptation\", \"data visualization\", \"chart type\", \"data tables\", \"token starter\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-foundations\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"motion\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-motion\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-motion/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-motion\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:motion\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"motion design\", \"animate this\", \"micro-interactions\", \"transitions\", \"interaction states\", \"hover state\", \"focus state\", \"loading state\", \"choreography\", \"motion budget\", \"AnimatePresence\", \"exit animation\", \"reduced motion\", \"morphing icons\", \"motion performance\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-motion\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"audit\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-audit\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-audit/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-audit\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:audit\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"design audit\", \"ui critique\", \"design review\", \"review the ui\", \"audit the design\", \"accessibility audit\", \"wcag contrast\", \"performance audit\", \"anti-slop detection\", \"ai tell\", \"production hardening\", \"design quality score\", \"ui quality review\", \"P0 P1 design findings\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-audit\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"md-generator\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"playwright-extract\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-md-generator\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-md-generator/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-md-generator\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:md-generator\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"extract design system\", \"generate design.md\", \"capture website css\", \"design tokens from url\", \"create design reference\", \"style reference\", \"tokens.json\", \"design-to-markdown\", \"extract design tokens\", \"validate design.md\", \"design.md validation\", \"design fidelity check\", \"design.md report\", \"render design preview\", \"source of truth\", \"study design.md format\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-md-generator\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"transport\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"od-cli-transport\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": null,\n      \"aliases\": [\"open design\", \"open-design\", \"od mcp\", \"od cli\", \"wire open design\", \"connect open design\", \"drive open design from the terminal\", \"design system from open design\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-mcp-open-design\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":165,"totalLines":165,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json","time":{"start":1783437244197,"end":1783437244202}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0076295aaea6008d016a4d17bc0670819181a7be5e352424d7"}},"id":"prt_f3d24b7240011TzdrUIfhcdQiD","sessionID":"ses_0c2dd1dfcffeawJ3GCJmwMFkLa","messageID":"msg_f3d248d2f001CSnH4zt1csBz6w"}}
